# Git commit messages (Atlas AI)

Follow `docs/guides/Code-Quality-Standards.md`, `docs/guides/Version-Control.md`, and `commitlint.config.js`.

## Format

```
<type>(optional-scope): <summary>

[optional body]

[optional footer]
```

- **Header** (first line) ≤ **100** characters
- Blank line between subject and body
- **Every body/footer line** ≤ **100** characters (wrap long sentences)
- Subject: imperative, concise; no trailing period
- English only

## Types

`feat` | `fix` | `docs` | `style` | `refactor` | `perf` | `test` | `build` | `ci` | `chore`

## Scopes (when useful)

`desktop` | `core` | `agents` | `tools` | `memory` | `database` | `shared` | `config` | `docs` | `scripts`

## Examples

```
feat(desktop): add Atlas shell greet IPC bridge
fix(config): resolve print script dist import path
docs: reorganize documentation structure
chore(deps): bump @tauri-apps/cli
```

## Agent commit workflow

- Only commit when the user asks
- Use a HEREDOC for the message (avoids shell eating backticks)
- Run hooks normally (Husky + commitlint); do not use `--no-verify`
- Do not commit `.env`, secrets, `.data/`, or model weights

## Bad patterns

- Long unbroken body paragraphs (fails `body-max-line-length`)
- Non-conventional subjects like `Updated stuff` or `WIP`
- Putting secrets or file paths with unescaped shell metacharacters in `-m "..."` without a HEREDOC
